note: Numerous stamps with the scribe's name appear throughout.
Catalog entry, number 186, pasted in (first front flyleaf recto).

msContents.summary: Genealogical tables and notes on the prophets and major Middle Eastern dynasties, including some Pre-Islamic dynasties. The tables begin with the Prophet MuhÌ£ammad and then recount the dynasties up to the year 1143 A.H. (1730), the year of the beginning of the reign of Sultan Mahmud I of Turkey. The genealogies between 1091 and 1143 A.H. were added in a different hand.

name.#text: Free Library of Philadelphia. Rare Book Department. John Frederick Lewis Collection of Oriental Manuscripts

supportDesc.extent: iii, 70, ii leaves : 310 x 216 (254 x 143) mm bound to 310 x 220 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation added in pencil, upper left recto including some flyleaves (1-72); catchwords every verso, lower left.

layoutDesc.layout: Numerous sets of concentric circles with a name written inside the interior circle and color filled in between the two circles connected by lines to other circle-sets. Text appears at angles among the circles. Several pages of prose history without roundels, chiefly 21 long lines.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, partially vocalized.

decoNote: Roundels are decorated with red, yellow and green dots and in-fill with red lines connecting them. Rubrications in red. Two headpieces in red and black (f. 48v, 49v).

binding.p: Bound in reddish brown leather over pasteboard with flap on the right side (Type II); blind stamped central mandorla and cornerpiece with matching stamps on flap; yellow laid paper doublure.

origin.p: Item was completed by Behmen Bek bin Ahmed Bek bin Yusuf Pasha in the city of Van on 7 Rajab 1091 (3 August, 1680) (f. 65v). The same colophon appears at the end of each prose section. The first colophon is dated 12 JumaÌdaÌ al-UÌlaÌ 1091 (10 June 1680) (f. 49r).

provenance: Sold at Sotheby's in February 1925 (note in pencil, first front flyleaf recto).
Formerly owned by John Frederick Lewis.

surface.@n: Fore edge flap closed, inside front cover
